From cou.: 5 In a DNA based molecular device, investigation of a transverse electric field or ferromagnetic electrodes broadens the underlying application of the device. In this paper we try to include a transverse electric field into the FM/DNA/FM device. The purpose is to get an enhanced or adjustable MR in a DNA device. Combining the work of Malyshev with that of Zwolak and Ventra, we study the MR of a FM/DNA/FM device with a transverse electric field by employing the lattice Green function and the Fisher-Lee relation. In section II the model and formula are presented. In section III the calculations are carried out and the discussion is given. Finally, in section IV a summary is made.
From Soup: 5 In a DNA based molecular device, investigation of a transverse electric field or ferromagnetic electrodes broadens the underlying application of the device. In this paper we try to include a transverse electric field into the FM/DNA/FM device. The purpose is to get an enhanced or adjustable MR in a DNA device. Combining the work of Malyshev with that of Zwolak and Ventra, we study the MR of a FM/DNA/FM device with a transverse electric field by employing the lattice Green function and the Fisher-Lee relation. In section II the model and formula are presented. In section III the calculations are carried out and the discussion is given. Finally, in section IV a summary is made.
