From cou.: 6 We consider a FM/DNA/FM device with the Hamiltonian,where Hmol describes the π-orbital of a poly(G)-poly(C) DNA molecule,34–36where c+G(C),i,σ(cG(C),i,σ) means the creation (annihilation) operator for an electron with spin σ at site i of base G(C), εG(C) is the on-site energy of a π-electron at base G(C) and tG(C) the hopping integral between the nearest-neighbor sites along each helix sub-chain. t⊥ is the hopping integral between the corresponding G and C bases of the sub-chains.
