From Soup: 87 The parameters are set as follows in this paper. For a poly(G)-poly(C) DNA molecule, the lowest unoccupied molecular orbital (LUMO) is taken as on-site energies: 33 ε G = 1.14 eV and ε C = −1.06 eV. The hopping integral is set as 34 t G ( C ) = 0.3 eV and t ⊥ = 0.1 eV, which are within reasonable parameter intervals. 35 We choose a typical tight-binding parameter for the ferromagnetic electrodes: 39 τ = 1.5 eV and J = 1.5 eV. The Fermi level of the electrodes is supposed to be at the middle of the DNA band gap. Interfacial couplings are supposed to be spin independent and set to be 0.02 eV, which is consistent with other theoretical works to fit the experimental I – V curves. 11 A low temperature of T = 30 K is applied in this work.
