From cou.: 88 n
From Soup: 88 We firstly investigate a one-helix-period poly(G)-poly(C) DNA which consists of 11-base pairs. Fig. 1 shows the current–voltage characteristics of the device for parallel (P) and antiparallel (AP) alignment of the magnetization of electrodes. The magnetoresistance is defined as MR = ( I P − I AP )/ I P . The inset in Fig. 1 is the corresponding dependence of magnetoresistance on applied bias. MR of the device increases from 3.1% at 1.2 V to 25.3% at 4 V. The result is consistent with that of ref. 31 . It should be mentioned that in ref. 31 the magnetization of the electrodes is characterized by the different hopping integral for majority and minority electrons, while here we describe the magnetization of the electrodes with different on-site energies. 39,40 There should be no qualitative difference for the final conclusion.
