From cou.: 96 We have performed a theoretical study of the quantum spin transport in a FM/DNA/FM device based on the lattice Green function method and the Landauer-Büttiker theory. We explore a possible usage of a transverse electric field for enhancing the magnetoresistance of the FM/DNA/FM device. It is found the direction and strength of the transverse electric field will induce a modulation in the MR. The MR of the device can be enhanced at some special direction and strength of the transverse electric field. This enhancement of MR is related to the electronic structure change induced by the transverse electric field, which is a peculiar characteristics of a DNA device.
